<manpage TITLE="initpw" SECTNUM=8>
<sect1>NAME 
 <P>initpw - Initialize the auth2 password database.



<sect1>SYNOPSIS<P>
<bf>initpw</bf> &lsqb;-k key&rsqb;


<sect1>DESCRIPTION<P>
<bf>initpw</bf> initialises the <em>auth2</em> password database by reading lines
from stdin and writing the corresponding database entries to stdout.
<bf>initpw</bf> supports the following command line options:
<descrip>
<tag><bf>-k</bf> <em>key</em></tag>Using the <bf>-k</bf> option allows
you to specify the encription key to use when encrypting clear text
passwords.
<P></descrip>

<bf>initpw</bf> expects to receive lines of the form:
<tscreen><verb>
&lt;ViceId&gt; &lt;Clear Password&gt; &lt;Other user info&gt;
</verb></tscreen>
Where:

<descrip>
<tag><bf>&lt;ViceId&gt;</bf></tag>is a Coda user id.
<P></descrip>
<descrip>
<tag><bf>&lt;Clear Password&gt;</bf></tag>is the password to use for
<em>ViceId</em>.
<P></descrip>
<descrip>
<tag><bf>&lt;Other user info&gt;</bf></tag>is other information about
the user you want to include in the <em>auth2</em> password database.
<P></descrip>


